## Plan: Add `mistral-instruct-v3` Template Handler

**Only `common/chat.cpp` needs to change** — two additions, no other files touched.

---

### Change 1 — New handler function (~line 1517)

Insert `common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3()` right after `common_chat_params_init_gigachat_v3`'s closing `}` (line 1517), before `namespace workaround`:

```cpp
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template &          tmpl,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string system_prompt;
    bool        is_first_user_msg = true;

    data.prompt = "<s>";

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            system_prompt = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            data.prompt += "[INST] ";
            if (is_first_user_msg && !system_prompt.empty()) {
                data.prompt += system_prompt + "\n";
                is_first_user_msg = false;
            }
            data.prompt += content + " [/INST]";
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            data.prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

- Builds `data.prompt` manually (no Jinja rendering needed)
- System message captured and prepended (with `\n`) only to the **first** user turn
- Produces: `<s>[INST] {system}\n{user1} [/INST] {assistant1}</s>[INST] {user2} [/INST]`

---

### Change 2 — Template detection (inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`, ~line 1644)

Insert after the Ministral-3 block, before the GPT-OSS check:

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v0.3 - uses [INST]/[/INST] markers without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
